By Salisu Sani-Idris  Abuja  –  FCT minister Muhammad Bello has described Mallam Abba Kyari, President Muhammadu Buhari’s late Chief of Staff, as a quintessential administrator whose wealth of experience would be greatly missed. Bello, in a statement issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Anthony Ogunleye, on Sunday in Abuja, described Kyari’s demise as a huge loss to Nigeria. The minister prayed God to grant eternal rest to Abba Kyari’s soul and grant his family the strength to bear the loss. (NAN) •The late Mallam Abba kyari The immediate past Director-General of the Nigeria Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA), Dr. Dakuku Peterside has described the death of the Chief of Staff, State House, Abuja, Mr. Abba Kyari as a big blow to President Muhammadu Buhari and indeed, all those who knew… April 18, 2020 In "News" Lokoja - Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi has condoled with President Muhammadu Buhari on the death of his Chief of Staff, Malam Abba Kyari. Bello sent the condolence message to the presidency on Saturday morning. In the message, the governor also sympathised with the people of Borno over the sad… April 18, 2020 In "News" By Ismaila Chafe Abuja,  -    The Presidency has described the reported resignation of the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari and the Director-General of the Department of State Services, Lawal Daura, as “mere distraction and pure mischief’’. Malam Garba Shehu, the Senior Special Assistant to the President… April 23, 2017 In "News"